title: Grateful Dead Live at Silva Hall, Hult Center on 1983-08-31
description: Alabama Getaway-> Greatest Story Ever Told, Dupree's Diamond Blues, Me & My Uncle-> Mexicali Blues, West L.A. Fadeaway, Hell In A Bucket, Althea, Cassidy-> Don't Ease Me In Cold Rain & Snow, Playin' In The Band-> China Doll-> Drums-> Truckin'-> Stella Blue-> Around & Around-> Good Lovin', E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text: Great show! I was never at this show,but love listening to it on a regular basis.If there is one thing worth checking out,its ths space.Check out the "Wang Dang Doodle"teases throughout the space.Of course,the "wang Dang Doodle" was played for the 1st time on Aug 26,1983 in Portland

Raw tribal space These 3 shows were a lot of fun , although I prefer the rest of the tour. I say its a 4 star show with ok sound . Not one of my favorites yet still good. If that even makes any sense. That said this night the space is raw and tribal to my ears. Kesey on THUNDER MACHINE, Phil in lobby of Hilton in the morning before our ride to Idaho. I was young and having time of my life back then. Before these shows we went to the cougar hot springs spent the afternoon kicking back with old earth people loving the experience. 
 Somewhere someone mentioned long rides in between shows well this was a loooooooong ride to Boise but oh so very worth it. The Boise show is in my top 5 along with Starlight theater in 1982. Speaking of long rides the ride in 1984 from Pine knob to Starlight was a very long ride with tragedy along the way. Sad but true we lived on the edge sometimes without even knowing it.

i cant get no ....satifaction caught this show, first of an out west tour that ended for mr in sante fe.... ,tickets were not to be had for the first 2 nights ..what,ya mean i cant just roll up and get tix the day of...ha,......i remember the double encore ,and after listening to this i can see why, the satisfaction has the crowd in full singalong mode,bobby cant find a place to fit in at the end,hahaha....this show, actually has a real kinda powerhouse feeling , great ending to this trio of shows in mellow downtown Eugene. i miss the days of "one more set,one more set..." ...on to Boise
